    <mxCell id="forecast" value="&lt;b&gt;48-HOUR CARBON INTENSITY FORECAST&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Three forecasting models are trained on 2019–2022 TVA grid data and compared:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Model 1 — ARIMA / SARIMA&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Statistical time-series model with 24-hour seasonal period.&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Serves as the statistical baseline for comparison.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Model 2 — Prophet (Meta / Facebook)&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Automatic daily, weekly, and yearly seasonality detection.&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Produces native confidence bands for uncertainty quantification.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Model 3 — XGBoost (Gradient Boosting)&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Uses engineered features: lags, rolling averages, calendar variables, fuel-mix lags.&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Typically the best performer on structured time-series data.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Models compared on holdout test set using MAE, RMSE, and MAPE.&lt;br/&gt;Best model selected for live operational use in the dashboard.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Output:  Predicted CI for every hour in next 48h + confidence bands (upper / lower)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Example:  Hour +0: 328 gCO₂/kWh  |  Hour +6: 201 gCO₂/kWh ✔ GREEN  |  Hour +14: 289 gCO₂/kWh"
      style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;align=left;spacingLeft=14;spacingRight=12;spacingTop=8;fontSize=12;verticalAlign=top;"
      vertex="1" parent="1">
      <mxGeometry x="500" y="1418" width="800" height="340" as="geometry"/>
    </mxCell>

