    <mxCell id="optimise" value="&lt;b&gt;OPTIMISATION ENGINE — TWO METHODS&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Method A — Greedy Heuristic (fast, real-time):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Find the earliest block of contiguous hours within the job's deadline window where&lt;br/&gt;the forecast CI is below the daily median. Assign the job to that window.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Input:  4 hours needed, 500 nodes, deadline: within 24 hours&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Best window found:  Hours 6–10  (avg CI = 201 gCO₂/kWh)&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;vs running now:  Hours 0–4    (avg CI = 328 gCO₂/kWh)&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Carbon saving:  (328 − 201) × energy_kWh / 1,000  =  X kg CO₂ saved&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Method B — Linear Programme (optimal, multi-job scheduling):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Minimise:  Σ [ x[j,t] × duration[j] × CI[t] ]  for all jobs j, hours t&lt;br/&gt;Subject to:&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;•  Each job runs exactly once within its deadline window&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;•  Total nodes in use at any hour t  ≤  total available nodes (4,626)&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;•  Urgent / time-critical jobs are never deferred&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Solver: PuLP with CBC (open-source, no licence cost)&lt;br/&gt;Output: Optimal start time per job · Minimised total carbon cost · Carbon saved vs baseline"
      style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d6b656;align=left;spacingLeft=14;spacingRight=12;spacingTop=8;fontSize=12;verticalAlign=top;"
      vertex="1" parent="1">
      <mxGeometry x="500" y="1808" width="800" height="370" as="geometry"/>
    </mxCell>

