    <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         KEY IMPROVEMENTS SUMMARY
    ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

    <mxCell id="improvements" value="&lt;b&gt;✅  SEVEN KEY IMPROVEMENTS OVER THE AS IS PROCESS&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;1.  Jobs are classified — delay-tolerant workloads (~30%) are identified and treated differently from time-critical ones&lt;br/&gt;2.  Grid is continuously monitored — 48-hour carbon intensity forecast updated every hour via EIA API&lt;br/&gt;3.  Scheduling is optimised — LP minimises total carbon cost across all pending flexible jobs within their deadlines&lt;br/&gt;4.  Carbon is measured — every job has a baseline carbon cost and actual carbon saving recorded in the audit log&lt;br/&gt;5.  CSRD-ready — hourly Scope 2 data captured and exportable for regulatory disclosure&lt;br/&gt;6.  Zero hardware cost — software-only change to the scheduling layer; no new infrastructure required&lt;br/&gt;7.  Replicable — the same system applies to any in-premise data centre running delay-tolerant workloads&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;(batch ETL, nightly backups, ML training, report generation, video transcoding)"
